---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About StillMotion"
	description="StillMotion is a single-purpose, privacy-first tool that turns any photo into a downloadable video clip, entirely in your browser."
	canonicalPath="/about"
>
	<section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
		<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">About StillMotion</h1>

		<div class="mt-6 space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:#5C4F3D;">
			<p>
				StillMotion does one thing, and does it well: it turns a still photo
				into a real, downloadable video clip. No account, no upload to a
				server, no watermark, no catch.
			</p>
			<p>
				We built it as a single-purpose tool on purpose. Instead of bundling
				dozens of unrelated utilities into one bloated app, StillMotion
				focuses entirely on one job &mdash; photo to video &mdash; so it can
				do that job faster, cleaner, and more reliably than a generic
				do-everything converter.
			</p>
			<p>
				Under the hood, StillMotion uses
				<strong style="color:#2B2013;">ffmpeg.wasm</strong>, a WebAssembly
				build of the industry-standard FFmpeg video engine, running entirely
				inside your browser tab. Your photo is loaded into memory, looped for
				the duration you choose, and encoded into a real MP4 or WebM file
				&mdash; all on your own device. It is never uploaded, transmitted, or
				stored anywhere.
			</p>
			<p>
				iPhone HEIC/HEIF photos are supported too: they're decoded locally
				using <strong style="color:#2B2013;">libheif-js</strong>, another
				WebAssembly library, before being handed off to the video encoder.
			</p>
			<p>
				StillMotion is free to use and supported by tasteful, non-intrusive
				advertising.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
